1. Install Pig

Go to official website:
http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html

Install Hadoop and Java in Requirements:
http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html#req

Download and install Pig:
http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html#Beginning+Pig

2. Set up working environment for Pig

Add JAVA_HOME environment variable:
$ export JAVA_HOME=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/jdk1.8.0_112.jdk/Contents/Home

Set Hadoop Home environment:
$ export HADOOP_HOME=/<my-path-to-hadoop>/hadoop-n.n.n
$ export PATH=$PATH:$HADOOP_HOME/bin

Add Pig Home:
$ export PATH=/<my-path-to-pig>/pig-n.n.n/bin:$PATH

Try the following command, to get a list of Pig commands:

$ pig -help
Try the following command, to start the Grunt shell:

$ pig 


3. Script Files
http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html#Sample+Code

Copy the /etc/passwd file to your local working directory:
$ cp /etc/passwd <my-working-directory>/

Creat id.pig, idlocal.java and idmapreduce.java as Sample Code.


4. Run Modes
http://pig.apache.org/docs/r0.7.0/setup.html#Run+Modes

Local Mode:
$ pig -x local id.pig

Mapreduce Mode:
$ pig id.pig
or
$ pig -x mapreduce id.pig

